  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved accessibility of basic primary health care services for Internally Displaced Populations and host communities in conflict-affected areas of Kachin State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will work in 6 IDPs camps and 13 host communities in NGCAs in Chiphwe, Hpa Kant, Shwe Gu, Tanai and Sumpra Bum Townships in Kachin State by supporting primary healthcare services for a total of 6,947 beneficiaries (Men:2204, Women: 2682, Boy: 1064, Girl: 997). Building on current HPA&#x2019;s capacities in the areas, a more comprehensive package of primary health care services will be combined into camp clinic and mobile outreach services activities including sexual and reproductive health with support for menstrual hygiene management and referral support. Working with existing structures of the local health departments and through community health volunteers, HPA will increase access to primary health care services for IDPs and host communities. HPA will provide technical assistance to the camp clinic and health staff from the EHOs to support improved primary health care services, while also advocating MOHS/WHO counterparts at national and state level to provide similar training for HPA health staff.
Community capacity building on rapid response mechanisms and contingency kits will be provided to enable them to better prepare and respond in the event of an emergency in the project intervention. Complaints and feedback mechanism will be developed with the community and beneficiaries will be encouraged to provide feedback. A community-based monitoring system will be strengthened to monitor health risks and the potential negative impact due to the program intervention through the complaints and feedback system.</narrative>
  </description>
